theres many things which i need to say, but first let me explain something. there are really only <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   six main roles</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> which make up the classes. those roles are as followed:<br>
<br>
-<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   damage mitigation</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->: the skill of damage avoidance. damage mitigation consists of stuns, slows and other debuffs, mezzes, charms, root, snare (when applied to kiting) and variants of these abilities. <br>
<br>
-<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   damage absorbtion</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->: the skill of tanking. damage absorbtion is a skill bestowed on those classes with high a defensive skill and good ac. all classes can absorb damage (obviously), but only melee classes can do it with any amount of efficiency (and in a more limited and situational sense pet casters). <br>
<br>
-<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   damage reperation</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->: the skill of replenishing hp. obviously, healing and regen spells fall in this catagory.<br>
<br>
-<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   damage dealing</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->: the skill of making things die. there are 2 ways to do damage; directly and indirectly.<br>
there are 3 ways to do direct damage. those ways are: pure slower but sustained, pure faster but resource based, or a hybrid of both.<br>
there is only one way to do damage indirectly, and that way is through attack speed or mana regen speed buffs.<br>
<br>
-<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   non-convienance oriented utility</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->. <br>
these are the situational types of supportive utilities which are <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   manditory</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> to acomplish some encounters, yet dont fall under the distinction of any of the above skills. such examples are pick locks and eb.<br>
<br>
*and*<br>
<br>
-<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   convienance oriented utility</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->. the skill of saving time and/or making situations generally easier. examples include coh, mana dumping, porting/tls, sow, resistance debuffing, corpse summoning, ect. a skill would be listed here, if you can answer the following question about it in the affirmative: &quot;does it make a situation easier, but is it not totally necessary to achieve the end result?&quot; <br>
the distinction between &quot;necessary and unnecessary&quot; is important and definative. <br>
in a limited sense, some forms of damage mitigation can be considered convienance oriented utility's more important older sibling.<br>
